  create a 'Composite' service. This is the coordinator.

  The Composite service calls the Product, Review, and Recommendation services, gathers all the
   data, and bundles it into one big response for the user.

  But what happens if the Review service crashes? We don't want the whole page to fail just
  because the reviews are missing.

  To fix this, I'm adding Resilience4j. This provides a Circuit Breaker.

  Think of it like the electrical panel in your house. If there is a surge, the circuit breaker
   trips and cuts the power to that one room so the whole house doesn't burn down. In our code,
   if the Review service is slow or broken, the Circuit Breaker 'trips.' The Composite service
  will then say: 'I can't get the reviews right now, but here is the product info anyway!'

  This makes our system 'resilient,' meaning it can survive partial failures."

